    <teiHeader><fileDesc><titleStmt><title>General Marshall to Mr.
                            Walter S. Robertson, at Peiping</title></titleStmt><sourceDesc><bibl type="frus-volume-id">frus1946v09</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-id">d723</bibl><bibl type="frus-document-number">723</bibl><bibl type="frus-div-subtype">historical-document</bibl></sourceDesc></fileDesc><profileDesc><settingDesc><setting><date notBefore="1946-08-01T00:00:00-05:00" notAfter="1946-08-01T23:59:59-05:00"/></setting></settingDesc></profileDesc></teiHeader><text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1946-08-01T23:59:59-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1946-08-01T00:00:00-05:00" n="723" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d723">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">Marshall Mission Files, Lot 54–D270:
                    Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">General <persName type="from">Marshall</persName> to Mr.
                            <persName type="to">Walter S. Robertson</persName>, at Peiping</hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Nanking</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1946-08-01">1 August
                            1946</date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>1224. Reference your 6268,<note n="24" xml:id="d723fn24">August 1, <ref target="#pg_1426">p. 1426</ref>.</note> since Nationalist and Communists
                    both wish to make a factfinding investigation, it appears advisable to send a
                    special team carefully selected especially as to American member.</p>
                <p>General Chou En Lai concurs in this message.</p>
            </div>
        </body>
    </text>
